WEBVTT

00:12.866 --> 00:18.093
Second Samuel chapter six, and I'll begin reading from verse six.

00:26.524 --> 00:34.815
When they came to the threshing floor of Na'khan, Azah reached out and took hold of the ark of God because the oxen stumbled.

00:35.336 --> 00:40.082
The Lord's anger burned against Azah because of his irreverent act.

00:40.162 --> 00:44.249
Therefore God struck him down and he died there beside the Ark of God.

00:45.150 --> 00:47.975
Then David was angry because of the Lord's wrath.

00:48.015 --> 00:49.838
It had broken out against Azah.

00:50.199 --> 00:55.387
And this day, that to this day, that place is called Perez Azah.

00:55.928 --> 01:01.938
David was afraid of the Lord that day and said, How can the Ark of the Lord ever come to me?

01:02.306 --> 01:06.952
He was not willing to take the ark of the Lord to be with him in the city of David.

01:07.352 --> 01:10.917
Instead, he took it to the house of Obed Edom, the Gittite.

01:11.578 --> 01:19.588
The ark of the Lord remained in the house of Obed Edom, the Gittite for three months, and the Lord blessed him and his entire household.

01:20.109 --> 01:21.651
This is the word of the Lord.

01:27.478 --> 01:28.479
Good morning church.

01:29.941 --> 01:30.642
Oh, wow.

01:30.786 --> 01:31.968
Yes, we're that church.

01:32.809 --> 01:33.390
I love it.

01:33.410 --> 01:34.010
I love it.

01:34.111 --> 01:35.412
It is an honor to be here.

01:35.452 --> 01:38.356
This is actually my first time in Portland.

01:40.119 --> 01:47.789
And my first brief exegesis of this area is your coffee is good and your sleeves are cuffed.

01:48.050 --> 01:50.453
So I'm happy to be here.

01:50.874 --> 01:52.215
My name is Faith Erie Cho.

01:52.296 --> 01:57.042
My family and I, we are in Northern New Jersey, 20 minutes from New York City.

01:57.346 --> 02:02.637
And yes, we are in the land of pizza, bagels, and coffee.

02:02.717 --> 02:04.180
So here we go.

02:05.804 --> 02:12.458
And as Tyler was reading that passage out loud, because, you know, when we prep these things, I read it in my head.

02:12.999 --> 02:18.130
I realize how it could be a bit of a damper on a Sunday.

02:18.210 --> 02:23.036
You know, you may be thinking, wow, is this like a fire and brimstone kind of a preacher?

02:23.376 --> 02:25.118
Or where are we going at here?

02:25.258 --> 02:26.480
What is she insinuating?

02:26.560 --> 02:29.844
Why are we learning about how Usa died?

02:30.365 --> 02:34.369
And David was mad, and Obed Edom was blessed.

02:34.510 --> 02:35.931
So what's the deal here?

02:35.951 --> 02:39.055
And what does it have to do with a present-centered life?

02:40.096 --> 02:42.479
And that's what I'm going to be talking about today.

02:42.519 --> 02:48.146
It's the present-centered life, a life of continual communion with God.

02:48.546 --> 02:58.902
I think the phrase that I want to point out here and highlight is when David says, how can the ark of the Lord ever come to me?

03:01.206 --> 03:04.110
How can the ark of the Lord ever come to me?

03:05.052 --> 03:07.495
This is his spiritual frustration.

03:07.535 --> 03:12.283
You see, David as a newly minted king had a vision.

03:12.343 --> 03:17.010
Now that he's about to start leading this kingdom

03:17.826 --> 03:25.539
And walking into his calling, he dreams of a kingdom that's centered around the presence of God.

03:25.579 --> 03:30.527
And so he knows that the presence of God is where the arc of the covenant is.

03:31.409 --> 03:34.915
And so he's trying to bring the arc towards Jerusalem.

03:34.955 --> 03:36.818
Now this is a great vision.

03:37.154 --> 03:41.361
It's like saying, I want to build a present-centered family.

03:41.421 --> 03:44.366
I want a Christ-like marriage.

03:44.627 --> 03:49.876
I want my job to honor God, and I want Jesus to be at the center of it all.

03:50.276 --> 03:52.099
I mean, this is a really good vision.

03:52.139 --> 03:53.682
So what gives?

03:55.202 --> 03:58.928
Like, what's with the diversion, God?

03:58.968 --> 04:00.870
I mean, isn't that a good desire?

04:00.931 --> 04:15.212
It's almost like the feeling that I get when I read this passage for the first time is, you know, when children raise their hands and they go up, and then, you know, if a parent ever goes, you know what?

04:16.153 --> 04:17.355
Let me just kill you now.

04:18.477 --> 04:24.626
You know, like, it's just, I could imagine this is extremely frustrating

04:25.666 --> 04:26.487
And you know what?

04:27.208 --> 04:29.852
Having a friendship with God is frustrating sometimes.

04:29.892 --> 04:30.373
Am I right?

04:31.755 --> 04:36.903
Because we sing these things and we say these things and we practice these things.

04:36.983 --> 04:42.451
But yeah, at the end of the day, He is a God that we cannot see and sometimes cannot hear and often cannot feel.

04:44.554 --> 04:50.604
And yeah, we are supposed to give Him our whole lives.

04:50.624 --> 04:54.930
There are a lot of spiritual frustrations that are normal in our faith.

04:55.042 --> 04:59.347
journey because at the end of the day God is mystical, am I right?

04:59.947 --> 05:03.411
Like he's not just a bridge that you see or a store that you walk into.

05:03.431 --> 05:08.036
Like he's mystical, he's beyond our human intellect.

05:08.457 --> 05:12.181
And sometimes he's beyond our understanding.

05:12.261 --> 05:24.114
I remember once I was turning off all the lights in my home and I was walking through the hallways and I heard some whimpering in my child's room and so I immediately go and

05:24.354 --> 05:27.399
I see her, she's on her knees, and she's whimpering.

05:27.419 --> 05:30.063
And I go, baby girl, what's going on?

05:30.724 --> 05:32.808
What's wrong?

05:32.868 --> 05:35.392
And she goes, he's stuck.

05:36.534 --> 05:38.236
And I go, what?

05:39.198 --> 05:40.220
Who's stuck?

05:40.861 --> 05:42.363
She goes, Jesus.

05:43.385 --> 05:48.132
Because at church, they said he lives inside of me.

05:48.333 --> 05:50.015
And I told him, you could come out.

05:50.055 --> 05:51.698
It's OK.

05:52.226 --> 05:53.589
Why are you stuck?

05:53.609 --> 05:54.531
He won't come out.

05:55.292 --> 05:57.476
I go, oh, my child.

05:58.779 --> 06:01.123
We've got to work on some theology here.

06:02.707 --> 06:08.658
But oftentimes, we ourselves are like, God, I gave you my life.

06:08.738 --> 06:10.382
I'm doing the lecture 365.

06:10.923 --> 06:12.626
I'm doing the morning midday.

06:12.674 --> 06:13.495
evening thing.

06:13.515 --> 06:16.979
And yeah, I still feel like something is missing.

06:17.059 --> 06:20.763
I don't enjoy worship like I should.

06:20.783 --> 06:25.128
I don't look forward when the app reminds me to pray.

06:25.148 --> 06:30.194
I rather just binge watch a documentary about a murderer.

06:30.274 --> 06:33.958
Like I just, I don't feel the pull, God.

06:33.998 --> 06:40.946
And we feel as though like, I love Jesus, but what does it take to be in love with Jesus?

06:41.538 --> 06:43.820
And that is oftentimes our frustration.

06:43.901 --> 06:55.713
I remember when I first got saved, it was such a romantic, fantastic, epic experience to the point where I told everyone, I'll never go back.

06:56.154 --> 07:01.840
And then I was so frustrated with how devastatingly normal life is.

07:01.860 --> 07:08.067
And I was trying to recreate these moments with God.

07:08.668 --> 07:10.930
Every Sunday, I wanted to be wowed.

07:11.458 --> 07:14.483
Like, tell me something I have never heard of.

07:15.124 --> 07:16.246
That's what I wanted.

07:16.306 --> 07:39.282
Until later, I realized that the gift of the gospel is not about accruing all-inducing revelations and collecting exciting moments, but rather, it's an intimate, authentic, and passionate friendship with Jesus.

07:40.834 --> 07:44.440
John 14 verse 17 says, he is the spirit of truth.

07:45.262 --> 07:50.791
The world is unable to receive him because it doesn't see him or know him.

07:51.613 --> 07:57.042
But you do know him because he remains with you and will be in you.

07:57.123 --> 07:58.004
That's the phrase.

07:58.465 --> 08:01.470
He remains with you and he will be in you.

08:02.352 --> 08:05.938
So when your daily practices are done,

08:06.690 --> 08:17.147
when you put your phone down, when you're no longer doing the pause, the sanctified pause that we're all aiming to do, the prayer does not end.

08:18.990 --> 08:24.759
The friendship is not on pause because he's still with you.

08:24.799 --> 08:28.245
He remains with you and will be in you.

08:28.365 --> 08:34.034
This is about a continual communion with the Holy Spirit.

08:34.114 --> 08:43.489
It does not end with your dedicated time of prayer, but it overflows into everything that you do.

08:43.529 --> 08:55.168
It is a lifestyle of keeping the lights on for Jesus perpetually, no matter what you are doing or who you are with.

08:56.290 --> 09:01.298
It's not about concentrating on him to the point of distraction.

09:03.298 --> 09:14.514
It's not just an interruption of your day with activities and programs, but it's a repurposing of your life.

09:15.816 --> 09:26.010
In order to cultivate a life that has continual communion with Jesus, it's not about just adding another program.

09:27.031 --> 09:31.698
We need to repurpose the whole thing, the whole life.

09:31.970 --> 09:46.365
But before I get into the practicalities of how we're aiming to do this, I want to clarify what I mean and what I hope all of us could at least think of when I talk about the presence of God.

09:48.308 --> 10:01.842
Because it's a phrase that we often sing about and we talk about, but for some of us it may be kind of confusing and we may not be sure why we say presence of God and not just God and not just Jesus at times.

10:02.050 --> 10:03.893
We're not talking about another entity.

10:03.933 --> 10:05.896
We are just talking about God.

10:06.436 --> 10:09.401
And as you and I both know, God is everywhere.

10:10.763 --> 10:11.704
God is everywhere.

10:11.744 --> 10:14.969
He is in the galaxies above and the craters below.

10:15.029 --> 10:16.150
He is everywhere.

10:16.210 --> 10:17.072
He is with you.

10:17.212 --> 10:17.973
He is with me.

10:18.113 --> 10:19.715
He is in the sky.

10:19.796 --> 10:21.919
He's in every hospital room.

10:21.959 --> 10:23.881
He is everywhere.

10:23.922 --> 10:25.624
He is transcendent.

10:27.607 --> 10:29.810
He is beyond our understanding.

10:30.050 --> 10:34.756
But just as much as God is everywhere, He is also somewhere.

10:37.038 --> 10:43.266
When we speak of the presence of God, we're talking about not just His transcendence, but His imminence.

10:44.607 --> 10:53.618
How He is omnipresent and infinite, and yet He's also relationally accessible to you and me.

10:54.946 --> 10:56.728
He chose to be Immanuel.

10:56.788 --> 10:58.050
He's God with us, right?

10:58.090 --> 10:58.931
That's Jesus.

10:59.372 --> 11:00.854
He also walks with us.

11:01.515 --> 11:02.596
He rescues us.

11:02.676 --> 11:04.719
He draws near to the brokenhearted.

11:05.700 --> 11:07.442
He's emotionally involved.

11:07.462 --> 11:10.787
He helps, provides, teaches, counsels.

11:10.847 --> 11:12.990
He dwells with us.

11:14.391 --> 11:17.516
So that's what we talk about when we're talking about the presence of God.

11:17.536 --> 11:19.378
And that's why we say, Holy Spirit, come.

11:20.322 --> 11:20.602
Right?

11:20.963 --> 11:22.064
Some of us may be confused.

11:22.084 --> 11:24.607
Like, why will we ask him to come if he's already been here?

11:24.687 --> 11:26.049
And he's been here before I was here.

11:26.109 --> 11:28.332
And, you know, that's what we mean.

11:28.912 --> 11:31.355
Because just as much as he's everywhere, he's also somewhere.

11:32.176 --> 11:34.940
And he is relationally accessible to us.

11:35.460 --> 11:35.661
Right?

11:35.701 --> 11:46.674
Now, to understand how to build a continual communion with God, I'm going to just kind of briefly run through how the presence of God dwelled with the community.

11:46.850 --> 11:48.532
throughout redemptive history, okay?

11:48.832 --> 11:52.075
So there's gonna be a list that goes up, hopefully.

11:53.476 --> 11:54.117
All right, there we go.

11:55.078 --> 12:02.845
The garden, the tabernacle, temple, and Jesus, and also the believers and the church.

12:03.466 --> 12:09.132
Wherever the Lord dwelled, when His presence dwelled, it was in these places.

12:09.232 --> 12:11.894
He walked in the cool of the day in the garden.

12:11.954 --> 12:15.858
He was in the most holy place in the tabernacle, then the temple.

12:15.970 --> 12:25.082
And then Jesus, who is both God and man, showed us what it looks like to be completely yielded and perfectly submitted to the Holy Spirit.

12:25.763 --> 12:29.728
And then now he's supposed to be in the center of every believer in the church.

12:31.110 --> 12:40.223
Wherever the presence of God dwelled long term, he was intentionally hosted.

12:43.086 --> 12:45.810
He's intentionally hosted.

12:46.914 --> 12:52.380
And wherever he is intentionally hosted, he is at the center.

12:53.381 --> 13:05.775
Not just physically, he's not just physically at the center, but the center of our orbit, the source of the gravitational pull that keeps everything together.

13:07.376 --> 13:09.439
He is the center of our purpose.

13:10.360 --> 13:11.501
He is our reward.

13:12.222 --> 13:13.363
He is our compass.

13:14.684 --> 13:16.306
So when I say center,

13:17.250 --> 13:20.614
Like I said, I'm not talking about just physical location.

13:20.955 --> 13:26.882
It's kind of like sometimes the center of a child's life is their basketball schedule or their soccer schedule.

13:27.663 --> 13:35.633
Sometimes the center of our lives is what our corporate job tells us it is supposed to be.

13:36.814 --> 13:46.546
So the center, the purpose, the compass, the reward, the gravitational pull of all things, what does your life

13:46.914 --> 13:48.155
orbit around.

13:48.736 --> 14:02.892
The way that he was at the center of the garden was Adam and Eve's ability to thrive and to expand the garden depended on their alignment with God's presence, their communion with God's presence.

14:02.912 --> 14:13.343
So if you will remember with me how it all began, God made Adam and Eve and then he breathed life into them and then he gave them the biggest homework assignment of all time.

14:14.525 --> 14:15.826
Now go and subdue the earth.

14:16.738 --> 14:18.160
You know, go take over.

14:18.200 --> 14:19.181
Go and be fruitful.

14:19.282 --> 14:20.183
Go expand.

14:20.483 --> 14:23.027
So they were supposed to expand this garden.

14:23.367 --> 14:33.722
But right afterwards, in Genesis 2, verse 3, it says, God blessed the seventh day, declared it holy, for honor he rested from all his work of creation.

14:35.304 --> 14:38.889
So first he gives them this assignment.

14:38.909 --> 14:45.618
And then they rest because he was prioritizing communion

14:45.954 --> 14:47.416
before productivity.

14:48.718 --> 14:54.405
And everything they were to do was to overflow from who they are with.

14:57.449 --> 15:07.262
Also in Genesis 3, 2 to 3, the woman said to the serpent, we may eat the fruit from the trees in the garden, but about the fruit of the tree in the middle of the garden.

15:07.983 --> 15:10.066
God said, you must not eat it or touch it or you will die.

15:10.338 --> 15:14.643
So we know on a physical level, the tree was actually in the middle.

15:15.063 --> 15:39.250
It was in the center of the garden, which is so poignant and beautiful because if you think about it, this garden was supposed to expand and thrive and be fruitful, but yet be centered on this choice for relationship at the very middle of the garden was this choice for relationship.

15:39.458 --> 15:48.532
Every time they passed the tree of the knowledge of good and evil, they had a choice to be perfectly aligned with God or go their own way.

15:49.975 --> 16:05.439
It kind of reminds me of the episode of Friends, I don't know if we're too holy for that here, but that one episode of Friends when Joey walks into a living room, when there's no TV, and he goes, what is all the furniture pointed at then?

16:06.901 --> 16:07.282
Right?

16:08.354 --> 16:15.184
Because for Joey, the purpose of a living room was to watch TV and to be in that lazy chair, right?

16:15.724 --> 16:23.395
The purpose of the garden was their communion with God, which is why it was at the center.

16:24.737 --> 16:27.681
He was also at the center of ancient Israel.

16:28.422 --> 16:30.545
And we see this first in the tabernacle.

16:30.986 --> 16:37.074
The purpose of the tabernacle was to host the presence of God in the wilderness.

16:37.186 --> 16:48.939
Now, for those of you that remember the wilderness story of the Israelites, some of us may think that the purpose of the wilderness was to get to the promised land when actually that was not the case.

16:49.119 --> 16:51.762
If that were the case, that journey would have taken 11 days.

16:53.064 --> 16:57.749
The purpose of the wilderness was the presence of God.

16:59.851 --> 17:04.977
In fact, you can see in the way they encamped around the tabernacle, okay?

17:04.997 --> 17:05.938
This is how

17:06.498 --> 17:09.581
When they're not traveling, this is how they all settled down.

17:10.482 --> 17:18.371
The tabernacles in the middle and everyone is just encamped around the presence of God.

17:19.833 --> 17:26.580
The purpose of Israel and their gathering and who they were was not to just be a great nation.

17:27.241 --> 17:31.606
It was not to just conquer the world, but it was to be God's people.

17:32.647 --> 17:33.728
That was at the center.

17:34.469 --> 17:35.410
Numbers nine.

17:35.874 --> 17:41.664
Verse 15 to 18 says, on the day the tabernacle will set up, the cloud covered the tabernacle.

17:42.025 --> 17:43.066
So imagine that with me.

17:43.086 --> 17:48.956
The 10th of the testimony and appeared like fire above the tabernacle from evening until morning.

17:49.638 --> 17:51.761
It remained that way continuously.

17:52.402 --> 17:55.848
The cloud would cover appearing like fire at night.

17:56.449 --> 17:59.154
Whenever the cloud was lifted above the Israelites,

17:59.746 --> 18:03.631
Above the 10th, the Israelites was set out at the place where the clouds stopped.

18:03.971 --> 18:05.633
There, the Israelites camped.

18:05.653 --> 18:09.838
At the Lord's command, the Israelites set out, and at the Lord's command, they camped.

18:09.938 --> 18:14.764
As long as the clouds stayed over the tabernacle, they camped.

18:14.784 --> 18:16.726
Now, so imagine this with me.

18:16.806 --> 18:19.309
This was the daily life of the Israelites.

18:19.870 --> 18:23.474
When they woke up, no one checked their eye count.

18:24.386 --> 18:26.369
No one checked their notification.

18:26.749 --> 18:28.872
No one checked their text message.

18:29.273 --> 18:33.719
They came out of their sleeping space and looked for the cloud.

18:34.840 --> 18:39.026
And whatever the cloud indicated was what they did that day.

18:39.506 --> 18:43.572
It determined their schedule, it determined their meal, they determined everything.

18:44.794 --> 18:48.318
They could not plan until they looked at the cloud.

18:50.301 --> 18:52.043
He determined everything.

18:52.704 --> 18:54.066
He was the compass.

18:54.594 --> 18:58.899
It wasn't the Promised Land.

18:59.300 --> 19:01.663
It was the presence that was the compass.

19:02.764 --> 19:06.789
He determined where they will go, what they will eat, how they will live.

19:07.930 --> 19:11.775
Now, after the wilderness, they were in the Promised Land.

19:12.776 --> 19:17.842
And the dream that David had that led to today's passage was

19:18.370 --> 19:21.294
a nation that was centered around the presence of God.

19:21.334 --> 19:25.140
And so what was the tabernacle eventually got transferred into the temple.

19:26.061 --> 19:41.424
So the holy of holies was to be in the temple and David's vision and Solomon's mission was to create a temple and this is where the presence of God was hosted and everything was to center around his presence.

19:41.444 --> 19:45.170
So the ancient Jewish life was profoundly impacted.

19:45.506 --> 19:49.311
by the temple of God, culturally, socially, economically, politically.

19:49.691 --> 19:52.454
It was a heart of Jewish identity and daily life.

19:53.135 --> 19:55.078
They had pilgrimage feast there.

19:55.158 --> 19:57.661
They had major life events there.

19:57.741 --> 20:00.464
They had teachings, public discourse.

20:01.425 --> 20:15.122
So what brings us to today's passage, this aim, this attempt at bringing the ark of the covenant, which was supposed to host the presence of God, it was the first big step

20:15.458 --> 20:19.983
towards this vision of a present-centered kingdom.

20:21.525 --> 20:28.193
And we arrive at this grave disappointment, fatal one.

20:29.695 --> 20:36.203
And we have three men highlighted here, Usa, David, and Obadietam.

20:37.224 --> 20:41.970
One died, one got angry, and one was blessed.

20:43.874 --> 20:55.428
And I would love to glean from their lives and this illustration of what it takes to live a life that's orbiting around the presence of God.

20:55.869 --> 21:05.400
Usa, the one that died, the center of his interaction with God was irreverence.

21:05.440 --> 21:08.023
It actually said that he died because of his irreverence.

21:09.165 --> 21:13.490
To him, he was just trying to handle

21:13.826 --> 21:17.409
a box that was about to fall off the cart.

21:17.830 --> 21:22.494
Now, for some of you that may hear about this and think, what's the big deal?

21:24.096 --> 21:26.298
Like, he was just trying to be helpful.

21:28.039 --> 21:29.761
Why did that deserve death?

21:29.861 --> 21:32.043
Now, I want to remind you who Uso was.

21:32.123 --> 21:34.205
He was a son of a binadab.

21:34.906 --> 21:43.794
The Ark of the Covenant was in a binadab's house before this, meaning Uso likely grew up around the Ark.

21:44.610 --> 21:47.434
which is why they had him and his brother lead the procession.

21:48.015 --> 21:49.597
Because they thought, well, you know the thing.

21:49.837 --> 21:52.401
You know how to handle this box.

21:53.683 --> 21:58.249
So you seem to be familiar with hosting the presence.

21:58.289 --> 22:00.392
It seems like you're familiar with it.

22:00.412 --> 22:03.997
And yes, Uso was familiar, but he was too familiar.

22:05.419 --> 22:10.226
Because to him, it was just a box to be handled.

22:12.162 --> 22:16.649
Just as for some of us, it's just a Sunday service to attend.

22:17.811 --> 22:19.774
For some of us, it's just a song.

22:21.396 --> 22:23.379
It's just Scripture.

22:24.240 --> 22:26.564
It's just Bible study.

22:27.165 --> 22:29.288
It's just community groups.

22:29.869 --> 22:32.433
It's just mid-day prayer.

22:33.314 --> 22:36.058
To Usa, it was just a box.

22:37.701 --> 22:41.266
His familiarity, breed,

22:41.634 --> 22:44.517
what was breeding an irreverence.

22:45.598 --> 22:57.470
And I wonder what areas of our faith journey is so familiar that we forget that it is God that we are interacting with.

22:58.871 --> 23:04.196
Now with David, what was at the center was his presumption.

23:05.037 --> 23:06.859
Yes, the vision was good.

23:06.899 --> 23:10.002
Yes, the intention was good.

